  "deferred": [
    {
      "kind": "guardrails",
      "reason": "Warranty-domain policies (no denial or warranty-exclusion routing of a claim implicating an open safety campaign; no denial conditioned on branded parts/service without causation evidence \u2014 the Magnuson-Moss tie-in rule; goodwill only within the documented matrix and approval tier; no supplier debit without attribution evidence) require guardrail-service / OPA policy materialization, which Core does not expose as a pack surface yet. The behavioral core is partially covered today by Core invariants: every pack-configured agent is proposal-mode with four-eyes approval (agent-runtime), and the agent instructions + disposition taxonomy route final determinations exclusively to human analysts with the Warranty Operations Manager as approver."
    },
    {
      "kind": "agent_recipes",
      "reason": "Bespoke LangGraph recipes (Claim Intake Copilot, Dealer Audit Analyzer, Early-Warning Signal Detector, Supplier Recovery Builder, Goodwill Advisor) require agent-runtime graph-module registration (BRD 23 BR-12). This pack specializes the existing case-triage + analytics agents via TenantAgentConfig prompt_params + tenant-scope RAG grounding instead."
    },
    {
      "kind": "connection_templates",
      "reason": "Production read connectors (OEM warranty systems: SAP Warranty Management / Oracle depot-repair-class modules; dealer management systems (DMS) claim feeds; telematics/hour-meter platforms; parts-return and failure-analysis tracking; supplier quality portals; NHTSA campaign feeds for vehicle OEMs) require customer credentials and pack-service connector materialization. The pack ships seed datasets in the exact landing shape; production connectors are configured through the product Data > Connections UI."
    },
    {
      "kind": "write_adapters",
      "reason": "Write adapters (post claim payment/denial to the warranty system, issue supplier debit memos, route a claim to a recall campaign, send dealer decision notices, order parts return for failure analysis) execute only behind pack-service's materialization contract and customer credentials; every such write stays proposal-mode with human approval \u2014 no autonomous claim payment, denial, or supplier debit, ever."
    },
    {
      "kind": "eval_sets",
      "reason": "Golden eval sets (claim triage, deadline-risk ranking, padding-signal detection, supplier-attribution classification, recall-routing accuracy) require eval-service write APIs whose action names are not yet in the rbac canonical catalog (Core follow-up noted in rbac catalog.go)."
    },
    {
      "kind": "ontology",
      "reason": "Ontology registration (Unit, Dealer, WarrantyPlan, Claim, LaborOp, Part, ComponentSystem, FailureMode, Supplier, SupplierChargeback, RecallCampaign, GoodwillRequest, AuditFinding) awaits pack-service; entity semantics are carried today by the warranty_core semantic model and dataset schemas."
    },
    {
      "kind": "case_schemas",
      "reason": "Typed case schemas (claim_adjudication, dealer_audit, supplier_recovery, goodwill_review, early_warning_investigation, recall_routing_review) await case-service schema materialization; today's cases carry the same fields via display_projection + the disposition taxonomy."
    },
    {
      "kind": "model_archetypes",
      "reason": "Model archetypes (claim_approval_confidence, dealer_padding_score, component_failure_hazard) await experiment-service archetype APIs; the scoring capability ships as pipeline seeds instead (isolation_forest unit anomaly + xgboost claim-outcome scorer) with model-governance expectations noted in grounding memories."
    },
    {
      "kind": "display_labels",
      "reason": "Display-label overlays (\"Claim\", \"Supplier chargeback\", \"Payment decision due\", \"Deadline at risk\", \"Recall routing\", entity templates) require the BFF label-registry endpoints (BFF-FR-082/088) which are pack-service-tier features."
    }
  ],
